ers, VHF DSC radio – how best to communicate at sea, Essential yacht tender safety for skippers and crew, Rig check – how to prevent failure at sea, Know your Navlights & Shapes – essential for all skippers, How to predict wind direction and strength by reading a weather chart, Anchoring – getting it right is not always straightforward, Safety Briefings – leave nothing to chance, Always have an emergency grab bag to hand when at sea…. Answer. However, if you don’t get it right, put it in a group that you will continue to visit more frequently. ... [PDF] Learn the Nautical Rules of the Road: An Expert Guide to the COLREGs for All Yachtsmen and Mariners Required fields are marked *. Diverso Impex - centar za … You will be taking … How to Memorize Quickly: The 5 Steps You Need To Complete This Week . Port Rudder Action Blast twice short, Turn to … Light characteristics – how do navigators identify lights at night? You’re connecting those neurons and dendrites in your brain, and you have a specific strategy for how to remember everything you read with the associations and things they remind you of. » Download How to Learn and Memorize English Vocabulary: . Every rule has. This rule is Rule 5 of the COLREGS and is often cited at the rule to remember at all times if any rule is to be remembered. What methods do YOU recommend for learning and remembering the ColRegs? Try these steps now, and you will find remembering things a lot easier, and you’ll memorize more than a lot of other people! Luckily, How to Build A Memory Palace is a core (and free) training that has you covered. I have no idea where I … This simplifies things: since both mnemonics refer to a double blast, you can just memorize that fact, and know that the other direction is the single-blast case. The United States Coast Guard has a comprehensive site called the Navigation Center where you can not only review the ColRegs … Putting facts to memory by brute force will not make you gain the most important resul